      "paper_id": "A74",
      "alloy_id": null,
      "description": "Laboratory smelting in a tubular furnace under argon atmosphere. Iron powder and ferrous oxalate were heated in an alumina crucible to 1873 K, held for 40 min. Deoxidizer added, then ferromanganese added and held for 20 min, followed by aluminum particles wrapped in iron sheet added and held for 60 min. Finally cooled to room temperature in the furnace. Al mass adjusted per heat.",
      "processes_notes": "Aluminum particles mass: 11 g for 1#, 28 g for 2#, 48 g for 3#. Iron powder base: 700 g. Ferromanganese: 225 g. Cooling: furnace cool."
    }
  ],
