  "unmapped_findings": [
    "The N content in steel decreases with the increase of Al content, while the O content slightly increases with the increase of Al content.",
    "The content of Si and Ti is ≈0.32% and 60 ppm in all three steels.",
    "In 1# sample, Al2O3-MnS composite inclusion number percentage increases with Al, while AlN-MnS and TiN-MnS number percentage decreases. Al2O3-AlN-MnS present in 1# and 2# but not in 3# sample.",
    "The number of inclusions with sizes between 1 and 5 μm accounts for 58.4%, 53.6%, and 48.2% in 1#, 2#, 3# respectively. Between 5 and 10 μm: 32.3%, 34.6%, 46.9%. Higher than 10 μm: 9.4%, 11.8%, 4.9%.",
    "Liquidus temperatures (TL): 1# 1702 K, 2# 1740 K, 3# 1796 K. Solidus temperatures (TS): 1588 K, 1560 K, 1532 K.",
    "Solidification route for 1#: L -> L + FCC -> FCC. For 2#: L -> L + BCC -> L + BCC + FCC -> L + FCC -> FCC. For 3#: L -> L + BCC -> L + BCC + FCC -> BCC + FCC -> FCC. Al expands BCC region and narrows FCC region.",
    "Solidification fraction for AlN precipitation: 0.46 (1#), 0.22 (2#), 0.51 (3#). For TiN: 0.89, 0.93, 0.94. For MnS: 0.77, 0.81, 0.85.",
